Description: Flash Android/Linux images to Rockchip RK3568 boards via Rockchip's upgrade_tool. Two transports — `windows` (default, runs upgrade_tool.exe via WSL→Windows interop, fast & proven) and `vbox-linux` (runs Linux upgrade_tool inside a headless VirtualBox VM that owns the USB device via VBox filter, useful when Windows USB driver is unavailable / on Linux-only hosts / for reproducible CI). Three subcommands per transport — `full` (whole-image factory flash from <bsp>/IMAGE/.../IMAGES/, follows official UL+DI sequence), `parts <p1> [p2]…` (single/multi-partition fast flash from <bsp>/rockdev/Image-*/), `auto` (mtime-diff: only re-flash partitions changed since last flash). Auto-detects the BSP repo by walking up from $PWD; auto-detects upgrade_tool.exe / Linux v2.4 binary from RKTools/. Uses `adb reboot loader` to enter Loader mode automatically (V+ button fallback when adb is offline). Optionally verifies boot via the uart-debug skill. Use when the user says /rk3568-flash, asks to flash/burn/program images to an RK3568 board, reflash boot/dtbo/super after a kernel/dtb/system rebuild, or recover a bricked board (via Maskrom + UPDATE button). Works with any Rockchip BSP repo that has `build.sh` + `RKTools/` at the root — no hardcoded paths, all config via env vars or auto-detection.
